        "paragraph_index": 0,
        "text": "## pKa Values of Citric Acid (NIST SRD-46)\n\nCitric acid (2-hydroxypropane-1,2,3-tricarboxylic acid, **ligand_9058**) is a triprotic acid defined as **H₃L** in SRD-46. Three measured pKa values are reported at **25 °C** and **I = 0.1 M**:\n\n| Step | Equilibrium | pKa | T (°C) | I (mol/L) | VLM ID |\n|------|-------------|-----|--------|-----------|--------|\n| pKa₁ | H₃L ⇌ H₂L⁻ + H⁺ | **2.90** | 25 | 0.1 | vlm_157473 |\n| pKa₂ | H₂L⁻ ⇌ HL²⁻ + H⁺ | **4.35** | 25 | 0.1 | vlm_157459 |\n| pKa₃ | HL²⁻ ⇌ L³⁻ + H⁺ | **5.65** | 25 | 0.1 | vlm_157439 |",
